		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Craig Childs</span></strong> lives with his wife and two sons in the West Elk Mountains of Colorado. He recently completed a descent of an uncharted river in Tibet: 180 miles of deep gorges, white water, and villagers aghast at his and his companions&rsquo; presence. He also enjoys long walks, the longest of which so far was 120 days in the Grand Canyon. His books include <em>House of Rain: Tracking a Vanished Civilization across the American Southwest</em> (Little, Brown and Company) and <em>The Way Out: A True Story of Ruin and Survival</em> (Back Bay Books).</p><a href="/contributors/craig-childs" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
